          "lecture_id": "graph_algorithms_001",
          "span": "A weighted directed graph assigns a numerical weight \\(w(u,v)\\) to each directed edge \\((u,v)\\). A path is a sequence of compatible directed edges. Its path cost is the sum of their edge weights:\n\n\\[\nC(v_0,\\ldots,v_k) = \\sum_{i=0}^{k-1} w(v_i,v_{i+1}).\n\\]"
        }
      ],
      "rationale": "The Path Cost Formula explicitly defines the cost of a path in a weighted directed graph, thus formalizing the concept of path cost within that graph model."
    }
  ]
